# ============================================================================
# INTEGRATION WITH OTHER COMMANDS
# ============================================================================

# The orchestrate hook works alongside other command hooks:
# - post-dev-feedback: Triggered during /orchestrate's dev phase
# - post-qa-retrospective: Triggered during /orchestrate's QA phase
# - post-release-monitoring: Triggered during /orchestrate's release phase
# - post-orchestrate-retrospective: Triggered AFTER all phases complete
#
# Hook invocation order in /orchestrate workflow:
#   1. /dev executes → post-dev-feedback hook (if eligible)
#   2. /qa executes → post-qa-retrospective hook (if eligible)
#   3. /release executes → post-release-monitoring hook (if eligible)
#   4. Workflow completes → post-orchestrate-retrospective hook (this hook)
#
# All hooks respect their individual trigger conditions and won't cause
# feedback fatigue if configured with appropriate filters.

# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================

# Issue: Hook not triggering on workflow failure
# Solution: Verify trigger_status: [failure] and enabled: true

# Issue: Hook triggering on success when you want failures-only
# Solution: Ensure trigger_status: [failure] (not [success, failure])

# Issue: Hook CLI not found error
# Solution: Install devforgeai CLI: pip install --break-system-packages -e .claude/scripts/

# Issue: Context extraction fails
# Solution: Check devforgeai/logs/hooks-orchestrate-{STORY-ID}.log for errors

# Issue: Performance slow (>200ms overhead)
# Solution: Ensure devforgeai CLI is installed (not running via python -m)

# For more troubleshooting scenarios, see:
# devforgeai/specs/STORY-026-TROUBLESHOOTING-GUIDE.md
